text: Kemp B. Johnson House is a historic home located near Fuquay-Varina, Wake County, North Carolina. The house was built about 1896, and is a 1 1/2-story, double pile, Queen Anne style frame dwelling. It has a high hipped roof and full-width front porch with intricate sawnwork decoration. A one-story, side- gable, three-bay wing was added about 1905. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2005. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina Category:Queen Anne architecture in North Carolina Category:Houses completed in 1896 Category:Houses in Wake County, North Carolina Category:National Register of Historic Places in Wake County, North Carolina
